const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What's the difference between a range, a stove, and a cooktop?",
    a: "Range is the freestanding or slide-in combo unit: cooktop on top, oven below, all in one chassis. Stove is the colloquial term, often used loosely to mean either the cooktop part or the whole appliance. Cooktop is the dedicated cooking surface that drops into a counter with the oven separately mounted in the wall. Different repair scope. Range repair is on this page; cooktop-only on /services/cooktop-repair/, oven-only (built-in wall oven) on /services/wall-oven-repair/.",
  },
  {
    q: "My gas range burner won't ignite, gas valve or igniter?",
    a: "Almost always the surface igniter, not the gas valve. Igniters wear at year 4 to 7 typical, you hear the click but no flame. $200 to $340 part plus labor. Gas valve failures are rarer (year 10+) and present differently: gas smell, valve sticking, weak flame. We diagnose with the multimeter at the igniter terminals first.",
  },
  {
    q: "My electric range oven won't heat, element or thermostat?",
    a: "Bake element burnout is the most common (year 7 to 10 typical), the element looks burned through visually or breaks the resistance test. Less common: oven temperature sensor drift (sensor reports cold while element runs constantly, or vice versa). Replacement bake element $200 to $360, sensor $200 to $340.",
  },
  {
    q: "My induction range cooktop went dead but the oven still works, what failed?",
    a: "Almost certainly the induction generator board (the inverter that drives the magnetic coils). Ovens on induction ranges run on standard resistive elements, totally separate from the induction electronics. Generator board failure $780 to $1,200 part. Bosch HEI series and Samsung NZ slide-in induction are the most common in LA, we carry parts.",
  },
  {
    q: "Pro-style range (Wolf, Viking, Thermador, BlueStar, Capital), worth repairing at year 12?",
    a: "Almost always yes. These ranges cost $8,000 to $15,000+ new and are designed for 18 to 25 year service lives with proper maintenance. A $700 control board on a 12-year-old Wolf DF range that costs $9,500 to replace is an obvious repair, not a replace conversation. We service all the pro-style brands and tell you straight when the math actually does shift toward replacement (very rare before year 18).",
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Bosch freestanding ranges?",
    a: "Yes. Bosch makes freestanding ranges for the US market: gas, dual-fuel, slide-in induction (HEI series most common). Some older industry references suggest Bosch is built-in only, that's outdated. We see Bosch freestanding ranges in modern LA kitchens, especially the slide-in induction in Westside coastal homes that converted to electric for energy compliance.",
  },
  {
    q: "How fast can you come for a range repair?",
    a: "Same-day across LA, Orange, Ventura in most cases. Phones answered 24/7. Dispatch scheduling 8 AM to 8 PM Mon-Sat. No emergency surcharge, $89 anytime. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410), BBB A+ accredited.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty on range repairs?",
    a: "90 days parts and labor on every repair. If the same component fails inside 90 days we replace it free, no fine print.",
  },
];

